# GMO Aozora API Specification Reference

Invoke `@gmo-spec` when you need authoritative information about endpoints,
request/response shapes, or error codes.

## API Base URLs

| Environment | Base URL |
|---|---|
| sunabar (sandbox) | `https://sandbox.apigateway.prod.gmo-aozora.com` |
| staging | `https://stg-api.gmo-aozora.com` |
| production | `https://api.gmo-aozora.com` |

API path prefix: `/ganb/api/corporation/v1/`

## Common Headers

```
x-access-token: <accessToken>              // Required for all protected endpoints
Accept: application/json;charset=UTF-8    // Required
Content-Type: application/json;charset=UTF-8  // Required for POST/PUT/PATCH
x-request-id: <uuidv7>                    // Optional but strongly recommended
```

## Authentication (OAuth 2.0 + PKCE S256)

```
Authorization endpoint: /ganb/api/auth/v1/authorization
Token endpoint:         POST /ganb/api/auth/v1/token
Revoke endpoint:        POST /ganb/api/auth/v1/tokens/revoke
```

Scopes:
- `private:account` — read account/balance/transactions
- `private:transfer` — create transfers
- `private:offline_access` — get refresh token

## Corporation API Endpoints

> IMPORTANT: GMO Aozora uses verb-based paths, NOT REST-style resource paths.
> `/transfer/request` is correct. `/transfers/{id}` is WRONG.

### Account Information

```
GET /ganb/api/corporation/v1/accounts
  Response: { accounts: Array<Account> }

GET /ganb/api/corporation/v1/accounts/balances
  Query: accountId
  Response: { balances: Array<{ accountId, bookBalance, availableBalance, balanceDate }> }

GET /ganb/api/corporation/v1/accounts/transactions
  Query: accountId, dateFrom (YYYY-MM-DD), dateTo, nextItemKey
  Response: { transactions: Array<Transaction>, nextItemKey?: string }
```

### Virtual Accounts

```
GET /ganb/api/corporation/v1/virtual-accounts
  Response: { virtualAccounts: Array<VirtualAccount>, nextItemKey?: string }

POST /ganb/api/corporation/v1/virtual-accounts
  Response: { virtualAccount: VirtualAccount }

PATCH /ganb/api/corporation/v1/virtual-accounts/{vaId}
  Body: { status }
  Response: { virtualAccount: VirtualAccount }
```

### Single Transfers (振込依頼)

```
POST /ganb/api/corporation/v1/transfer/request
  Body: TransferCreateInput
  Response: { accountId, resultCode, applyNo, applyEndDatetime? }

GET /ganb/api/corporation/v1/transfer/status
  Query: accountId, queryKeyClass, applyNo?, dateFrom?, dateTo?, nextItemKey?
  Response: { accountId, transferStatusList: Array<TransferStatusItem>, nextItemKey? }

GET /ganb/api/corporation/v1/transfer/request-result
  Query: accountId, applyNo
  Response: { accountId, resultCode, applyNo, applyEndDatetime? }

POST /ganb/api/corporation/v1/transfer/transferfee
  Body: TransferCreateInput
  Response: { accountId, baseDate, baseTime, totalFee, transferFeeDetails }

POST /ganb/api/corporation/v1/transfer/cancel
  Body: { accountId, cancelTargetKeyClass, applyNo }
  Response: { accountId, resultCode, applyNo, applyEndDatetime? }
```

### Bulk Transfers (総合振込依頼)

```
POST /ganb/api/corporation/v1/bulktransfer/request
  Body: BulkTransferCreateInput
  Response: { accountId, resultCode, applyNo, applyEndDatetime? }

GET /ganb/api/corporation/v1/bulktransfer/status
  Query: accountId, queryKeyClass, applyNo?, dateFrom?, dateTo?, nextItemKey?
  Response: { accountId, transferStatusList: Array<BulkTransferStatusItem>, nextItemKey? }

GET /ganb/api/corporation/v1/bulktransfer/request-result
  Query: accountId, applyNo
  Response: { accountId, resultCode, applyNo, applyEndDatetime? }

POST /ganb/api/corporation/v1/bulktransfer/transferfee
  Body: BulkTransferCreateInput
  Response: { accountId, baseDate, baseTime, totalFee, transferFeeDetails }

POST /ganb/api/corporation/v1/bulktransfer/cancel
  Body: { accountId, cancelTargetKeyClass, applyNo }
  Response: { accountId, resultCode, applyNo, applyEndDatetime? }
```

## Field Conventions

- Amounts: strings, e.g. `"5800"` (never numbers)
- Dates: `YYYY-MM-DD` strings
- Timestamps: ISO 8601 strings
- Account IDs: strings, 12–29 digits
- Apply numbers: 16-digit numeric strings
- Bank codes: 4-digit strings, e.g. `"0310"` for GMO Aozora
- Branch codes: 3-digit strings
- Account numbers: 7-digit strings (zero-padded)

## Result Codes

- `'1'` = 完了 (completed successfully)
- `'2'` = 未完了 (still processing — poll `/request-result`)
- `'8'` = 期限切れ (expired — no longer available)

## Common Error Codes

| HTTP Status | GMO Error Code | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| 400 | `INVALID_PARAMETER` | Bad request parameters |
| 401 | `UNAUTHORIZED` | Token invalid/expired |
| 403 | `FORBIDDEN` | Insufficient scope |
| 404 | `NOT_FOUND` | Resource not found |
| 409 | `CONFLICT` | Duplicate request ID |
| 429 | `TOO_MANY_REQUESTS` | Rate limit exceeded |
| 500 | `INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR` | Server error (retry) |

## Spec Versions

This file covers API spec **v1.8.0**. If GMO releases a new spec version,
update the schemas and this reference, then bump the SDK minor version.
